    <p class="section-tag">Guide</p>
    <h1 class="mb-6">How to Appear in Claude AI</h1>

    <img src="/images/content/five-signal-model.svg" alt="The Five Signal Model for AI search" class="w-full rounded-xl mb-8 mt-6" loading="lazy">

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Claude, built by Anthropic, draws from indexed web content and training data. It values clear entity definition and multiple independent sources describing the business consistently.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Claude tends to be more cautious than ChatGPT in its recommendations. It will often qualify its answers with caveats about verification. This means businesses with the strongest, most verifiable entity signals perform best.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Our analysis of 1,400+ UK businesses through Rank4AI reveals fascinating patterns in how Claude evaluates entities. Unlike other AI systems, Claude shows a clear preference for businesses with multiple verification touchpoints.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">What Claude Looks For</h2>

<h3>Consistent Entity Definition</h3>
<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Claude cross-references how a business is described across multiple sources. Inconsistency reduces confidence significantly. When your business name, services, or location details vary between platforms, Claude flags this as unreliable.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">For example, if your website lists "Digital Marketing Services" but your Google Business Profile shows "SEO Consultancy", Claude struggles to define what you actually do. This confusion directly impacts recommendation likelihood.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">From our Rank4AI data, businesses with 95%+ consistency across platforms receive 40% more Claude recommendations than those with mixed messaging.</p>

<h3>Verifiable Information</h3>
<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Claude prioritises information it can verify from multiple independent sources. Claims that only appear on your own website carry less weight. Third-party validation becomes crucial for Claude's confidence scoring.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Consider two plumbing companies. Company A claims "20 years experience" only on their website. Company B has this verified through industry directories, customer reviews, and news articles. Claude recommends Company B more frequently.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Independent verification sources Claude values include:</p>
<ul class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">
  <li>Industry directories and associations</li>
  <li>News publications and press coverage</li>
  <li>Customer review platforms</li>
  <li>Professional accreditation bodies</li>
  <li>Government registrations and certifications</li>
</ul>

<h3>Structured Expertise</h3>
<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Depth of content in a specific area signals specialisation. Claude recommends specialists more confidently than generalists. Businesses that demonstrate deep knowledge in narrow fields outperform those covering broad topics superficially.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">A law firm specialising exclusively in employment law with 50 detailed articles will outrank a general practice with 200 basic legal tips. Claude interprets depth as authority.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Building Claude-Optimised Entity Signals</h2>

<h3>Create Comprehensive Business Profiles</h3>
<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Start with your foundational business information. Ensure every detail remains identical across all platforms. This includes your exact business name, address format, phone number, and service descriptions.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Create a master document containing your standard business details. Use this template for every directory submission, social media profile, and website page. Consistency builds Claude's confidence in your entity.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Key platforms requiring consistent information:</p>
<ul class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">
  <li>Google Business Profile</li>
  <li>Companies House registration</li>
  <li>Industry-specific directories</li>
  <li>Social media business pages</li>
  <li>Review platforms like Trustpilot</li>
  <li>Local business directories</li>
</ul>

<h3>Develop Third-Party Validation</h3>
<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Claude heavily weights information from independent sources. Focus on building mentions and references beyond your own controlled content. This requires strategic relationship building and thought leadership.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Effective third-party validation strategies include:</p>
<ul class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">
  <li>Guest posting on industry publications</li>
  <li>Speaking at conferences and events</li>
  <li>Participating in industry surveys and reports</li>
  <li>Joining professional associations</li>
  <li>Earning industry awards and certifications</li>
  <li>Collaborating with other businesses</li>
</ul>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">One accountancy firm increased Claude mentions by 60% after joining three professional bodies and contributing to two industry publications. The independent validation transformed their AI visibility.</p>

<h3>Establish Topical Authority</h3>
<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Claude responds well to demonstrated expertise in specific domains. Rather than covering everything, choose 2-3 core topics and create comprehensive content around them.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Map your expertise areas and create content clusters. Each cluster should contain 10-20 pieces covering different aspects of the same topic. This depth signals specialisation to Claude's algorithms.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">For example, a cybersecurity consultancy might focus on:</p>
<ul class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">
  <li>GDPR compliance for small businesses</li>
  <li>Ransomware prevention strategies</li>
  <li>Cloud security implementations</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Common Claude Optimisation Mistakes</h2>

<h3>Inconsistent Business Information</h3>
<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">The most frequent error we see in Rank4AI audits involves mismatched business details. Small variations in company names or addresses confuse Claude's entity recognition.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">"Smith & Associates Ltd" on your website but "Smith and Associates Limited" on directories creates entity ambiguity. Claude may treat these as separate businesses, diluting your authority signals.</p>

<h3>Over-Reliance on Own Content</h3>
<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Many businesses focus exclusively on their own website content. While important, Claude discounts information without external validation. Self-published content alone cannot establish entity authority.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Balance your content strategy. For every five pieces you publish, aim for at least one external mention or collaboration. This ratio helps Claude verify your expertise claims.</p>

<h3>Broad Topic Coverage</h3>
<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Attempting to cover too many topics dilutes your expertise signals. Claude prefers businesses with clear specialisations over those claiming to do everything.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">A marketing agency covering SEO, PPC, social media, web design, branding, and PR appears unfocused to Claude. Narrowing to 2-3 core services builds stronger entity signals.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Measuring Claude Performance</h2>

<h3>Entity Recognition Testing</h3>
<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Regularly test how Claude recognises and describes your business. Ask specific questions about your services, location, and expertise. Note any inconsistencies or gaps in Claude's knowledge.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Create a monthly testing routine. Document Claude's responses and track improvements over time. This data helps identify which optimisation efforts produce results.</p>

<h3>Recommendation Frequency Analysis</h3>
<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Monitor how often Claude recommends your business for relevant queries. Test various question formats and track recommendation patterns. Look for improvements in both frequency and confidence levels.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Our <a href="/free-audit/">free audit tool</a> includes Claude-specific testing scenarios. This analysis reveals your current performance and highlights improvement opportunities.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Advanced Claude Strategies</h2>

<h3>Structured Data Implementation</h3>
<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Claude responds well to structured data markup. Implement schema.org markup for your business information, services, and content. This helps Claude understand your entity relationships more clearly.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Focus on LocalBusiness, Organization, and Service schema types. These provide Claude with explicit entity information, reducing interpretation errors.</p>

<h3>Citation Network Development</h3>
<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Build a comprehensive citation network across relevant directories. Claude uses these consistent mentions to verify your business existence and services.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Target industry-specific directories over generic ones. A solicitor benefits more from Law Society listings than general business directories. Quality citations outweigh quantity for Claude.</p>

<h3>Knowledge Graph Integration</h3>
<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Work towards inclusion in knowledge graphs like Wikidata or industry databases. These authoritative sources significantly boost Claude's confidence in your entity.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">While challenging to achieve, knowledge graph inclusion represents the highest level of entity validation. Start by building relationships with organisations that contribute to these databases.</p>

<h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Key Takeaways</h2>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Claude requires consistent, verifiable entity signals to recommend businesses confidently. Focus on building authority through independent validation rather than self-promotion alone.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Key priorities for Claude optimisation include:</p>

<ul class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">
  <li>Maintaining identical business information across all platforms</li>
  <li>Developing third-party validation through industry participation</li>
  <li>Creating deep expertise content in narrow specialisation areas</li>
  <li>Building comprehensive citation networks</li>
  <li>Testing and measuring Claude recognition regularly</li>
</ul>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Claude's cautious approach rewards businesses with strong foundational entity signals. Invest time in building these foundations before pursuing advanced tactics.</p>

<p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Start with our comprehensive AI visibility audit to understand your current Claude performance and identify immediate improvement opportunities.</p>

